    "To date, LLMs cannot be used to replace research subjects, at least not without further specifications nor without taking precautions in the use of the results.",
    "This does not mean that LLMs are either useless for social science on other tasks (Bail, 2024), or altogether incapable of capturing social regularities.",
    "Strimling et al. (2024) show for instance that GPT-4 is able to output the dominant view on certain moral topics with a reasonable success rate, at least at the country level.",
    "Sometimes, the demands placed on the model are more limited: when asked to imitate what is considered a universal reaction to a signal, LLM simulations may be informative. 24",
